scripts.script:
#!/bin/bash

# Check current appearance mode
current_mode=$(osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" to tell appearance preferences to get dark mode')

if [ "$current_mode" = "true" ]; then
  # Switch to Light mode
  osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" to tell appearance preferences to set dark mode to false'
  echo "Switched to Light Mode"
else
  # Switch to Dark mode
  osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" to tell appearance preferences to set dark mode to true'
  echo "Switched to Dark Mode"
fi

scripts.name: HEIC to JPG
scripts.description:
🖼️ HEIC to JPEG Converter Automation

This automation allows you to quickly convert one or more .HEIC image files to .JPEG format using a script and macOS’s built-in tools. You simply select the images in Finder, run the script, and the converted images will appear in a folder on your Desktop.

scripts.script:
-- Get the selected file in Finder
tell application "Finder"
	set theSelection to selection
	if theSelection is {} then
		display dialog "Please select a video file in Finder." buttons {"OK"} default button 1
		return
	end if
	set inputFile to POSIX path of (item 1 of theSelection as alias)
end tell

-- Define output folder and file
set outputFolder to POSIX path of (path to desktop folder) & "MP4_Output/"
do shell script "mkdir -p " & quoted form of outputFolder

-- Extract filename and prepare output path
do shell script "/usr/bin/basename " & quoted form of inputFile & " .mov"
set baseName to the result
set outputFile to outputFolder & baseName & ".mp4"

-- Run FFmpeg in Terminal with progress
tell application "Terminal"
	activate
	do script "ffmpeg -i " & quoted form of inputFile & " -c:v libx264 -c:a aac -vf format=yuv420p -movflags +faststart " & quoted form of outputFile
end tell
scripts.name: MOV to MP4
scripts.description: This macOS automation streamlines the process of converting .mov video files to .mp4 format using FFmpeg. Simply select a video file in Finder, run the automation, and it will automatically create a folder on your Desktop (MP4_Output) to store the converted file. The conversion uses efficient encoding settings for wide compatibility and fast playback (libx264, aac, yuv420p, and +faststart). Progress is shown in Terminal, giving you real-time feedback. Ideal for batch processing video clips or preparing media for web and mobile use.

scripts.name: Add Watermark
scripts.script:
set watermarkText to "© YourName 2025"
set watermarkPercentage to 5 -- Percentage of the image width

tell application "Adobe Photoshop 2025"
    activate
    set docRef to current document
    tell docRef
        -- Calculate watermark size as a percentage of the image width
        set watermarkSize to (docRef's width * watermarkPercentage) / 100
        
        make new art layer with properties {kind:text layer}
        set contents of text object of current layer to watermarkText
        set position of text object of current layer to {50, docRef's height - 50}
        set size of text object of current layer to watermarkSize
        set opacity of current layer to 50
    end tell
end tell
scripts.description: Automatically apply your custom watermark to images in Photoshop 2025 with a single action. This automation opens your files, inserts a predefined watermark (text or image), positions it precisely (e.g., bottom-right corner), adjusts opacity for subtle branding, and saves the result—ready for publishing or sharing. Perfect for photographers, designers, and content creators who want to protect their work and maintain a consistent visual identity without repetitive manual steps.

scripts.script:
set exportFolder to choose folder with prompt "Choose folder to save flattened copies:"

tell application "Adobe Photoshop 2025"
	activate
	repeat with docRef in documents
		tell docRef
			flatten
			set exportName to name
			set exportPath to (exportFolder as text) & "flat-" & exportName
			set jpegOptions to {class:JPEG save options, quality:10}
			save in file exportPath as JPEG with options jpegOptions
		end tell
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.name: Flatten All
scripts.description: Quickly flatten all layers in your Photoshop 2025 project with a single automated action. Eliminate the hassle of manual layer merging and streamline your workflow with one click.

	activate
	repeat with docRef in documents
		tell docRef
			set docName to name
			if docName does not end with ".psd" then set docName to docName & ".psd"
			set savePath to backupFolder as text & "backup-" & docName
			save in file savePath as Photoshop format
		end tell
	end repeat
end tell

scripts.script:
tell application "Keynote"
	activate
	set doc to front document
	repeat with s in slides of doc
		tell s
			make new text item with properties {object text:"Your Footer Text", position:{50, 1000}, width:600}
		end tell
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.name: Add footer
scripts.description: Adds footer for every keynote slide that is in the project. Define your own text and placement of the footer by changing the values in the script.

scripts.script:
tell application "Keynote"
	set doc to front document
	set slideCount to count of slides of doc
	repeat with i from 1 to slideCount
		set thisSlide to slide i of doc
		set currentTitle to object text of default title item of thisSlide
		set object text of default title item of thisSlide to ("Slide " & i & ": " & currentTitle)
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.name: Prefix For Slide Title
scripts.description: Adds a prefix for all slide titles.

scripts.script:
tell application "Keynote"
	activate
	set doc to front document
	start doc
end tell
scripts.name: Start Presentation
scripts.description: Starts Keynote presentation from the first slide.

scripts.script:
tell application "Audacity" to activate
delay 1
tell application "System Events"
    keystroke "n" using {command down} -- New project
    delay 0.5
    keystroke "r" -- Start recording
end tell
scripts.name: Open Audacity and Start New Recording
scripts.description: Opens Audacity and automatically starts recording.

scripts.script:
tell application "Audacity" to activate
delay 1
tell application "System Events"
    keystroke "a" using {command down} -- Select all
    delay 0.5
    keystroke "n" using {shift down, command down} -- Normalize (custom shortcut if set)
    delay 2
    keystroke "e" using {shift down, command down} -- Export
    delay 1
    keystroke "w" -- Select WAV format
    delay 0.5
    keystroke return -- Confirm
end tell
scripts.name: Normalize and Export Selected Audio to WAV
scripts.description: Selects all, then normalize and then export selected audio to WA.

scripts.script:
tell application "Audacity" to activate
delay 1
tell application "System Events"
    keystroke "s" using {command down} -- Save
    delay 1
    keystroke "w" using {command down} -- Close window
end tell
scripts.name: Automated Save and Close Project
scripts.description: Saves and closes the project.

scripts.script:
tell application "System Events"
    tell process "Audacity"
        set frontmost to true
        -- Split at the cursor position (default: Command + I)
        keystroke "i" using {command down}
    end tell
end tell
scripts.name: Slice (Split) Audio at Current Selection Point
scripts.description: This triggers Audacity’s “Split” function (Edit > Clip Boundaries > Split), which slices the selected track at the current cursor position or within a selected range.

scripts.name: Move Emails from a Specific Sender to a Folder
scripts.script:
tell application "Mail"
	set targetMailbox to mailbox "ENTER_MAILBOX" of account "iCloud"
	set selectedMessages to messages of inbox whose sender contains "example@domain.com"
	repeat with msg in selectedMessages
		move msg to targetMailbox
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.description:
Moves email from specified inbox to a selected folder.
Specify your mailbox and replace ENTER_MAILBOX field.
Specify the email of the messages you want to move by replacing example@domain.com.

scripts.name: Archive All Read Emails Older Than 7 Days
scripts.script:
set daysOld to 7
set cutoffDate to (current date) - (daysOld * days)

tell application "Mail"
	set inboxMessages to messages of inbox
	repeat with msg in inboxMessages
		if read status of msg is true and date received of msg is less than cutoffDate then
			move msg to mailbox "Archive" of account "iCloud"
		end if
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.description: Automatically declutter your inbox by moving older, read messages to Archive.

scripts.name: Reply with a Standard Template
scripts.script:
set replyText to "Thank you for your message. I’ll get back to you as soon as I can."

tell application "Mail"
	set selectedMessages to selection
	repeat with msg in selectedMessages
		set theReply to reply msg with opening window
		set content of theReply to replyText
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.description:
Replies to selected emails with a predefined message.
Replace reply Text for message you want to send.

scripts.name: Export Attachments from Selected Emails
scripts.script:
set savePath to "/Users/MailAttachments/"

tell application "System Events"
	if not (exists folder savePath) then
		do shell script "mkdir -p " & quoted form of savePath
	end if
end tell

tell application "Mail"
	set selectedMessages to selection
	repeat with msg in selectedMessages
		repeat with anAttachment in mail attachments of msg
			set attachmentName to name of anAttachment
			set fullPath to savePath & attachmentName
			set fileRef to (fullPath as POSIX file) -- This now works because we don’t force alias
			try
				save anAttachment in fileRef
			on error errMsg number errNum
				display dialog "❌ Failed to save: " & attachmentName & return & errMsg
			end try
		end repeat
	end repeat
end tell
scripts.description: Saves attachments from selected messages to a designated folder.
